                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_bærkad" xml:lang="os"><form type="lemma"><orth>bærkad</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>изобилие (о домашнем хозяйстве)</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>abundance (of housekeeping)</q></tr></sense><exampleGrp><example><quote>wæ bærkad biræ<note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (обычная формула благодарности за угощение)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (a usual form of thanking for food)</note></quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>да умножится ваш %sbærkаd%s</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>may your %sbærkаd%s multiply</q></tr></example><example><quote>fynǵy bærkad</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>неиссякаемое изобилие стола</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>inexhaustible abundance of meal</q></tr></example><example><quote>ʒag xoræj mæ xordon, bærkadǵyn mæ zæxx</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>полна хлеба моя житница, изобильна моя земля</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>my granary is full of bread, my ground is abundant</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>15</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><exampleGrp><example><quote>wæ bærkad biræ<note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (обычная формула благодарности за угощение)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (a usual form of thanking for food)</note></quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>да умножится ваш %sbærkаd%s</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>may your %sbærkаd%s multiply</q></tr></example><example><quote>fynǵy bærkad</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>неиссякаемое изобилие стола</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>inexhaustible abundance of meal</q></tr></example><example><quote>ʒag xoræj mæ xordon, bærkadǵyn mæ zæxx</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>полна хлеба моя житница, изобильна моя земля</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>my granary is full of bread, my ground is abundant</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>15</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Из <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/> <w>barakat</w> <gloss><q>изобилие</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""><w/> <gloss><q>благоденствие</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""><w/> <gloss><q>довольство</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/> <w>barakad</w></mentioned>. Распространено по всему Кавказу: <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/> <w>berakat</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""><w>bierkat</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/> <w>barkàt</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lbe"><lang/> <w>baračat</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/> <w>bereket</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""><w>baraket</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>baraka</w></mentioned>. В осетинский это слово было заимствовано дважды: сперва в форме %ibærkad%i (через дагестанское посредство, ср. <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/> <w>barkàt</w></mentioned>), позднее в форме <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bæræḱet"/> | %ibereket%i (через кабардинское посредство, ср. <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/> <w>baraket</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><w>bereket</w></mentioned>, ). Ср. другие случаи двукратного заимствования одного и того же слова: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærx"/> и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_lawyz"/> и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_lwasi"/> и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼalati"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>93</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">From <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/> <w>barakat</w> <gloss><q>abundance</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""><w/> <gloss><q>welfare</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""><w/> <gloss><q>contentment</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/> <w>barakad</w></mentioned>. The word is widespread all over the Caucasus: <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/> <w>berakat</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""><w>bierkat</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/> <w>barkàt</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lbe"><lang/> <w>baračat</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/> <w>bereket</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""><w>baraket</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>baraka</w></mentioned>. The word was borrowed in Ossetic twice: firstly, in the form %ibærkad%i (through Dagestan, cf. <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/> <w>barkàt</w></mentioned>), later in the form <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bæræḱet"/> | %ibereket%i (through Kabardian, cf. <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/> <w>baraket</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><w>bereket</w></mentioned>, ). Cf. other cases of double borrowing of the same word: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærx"/> and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_lawyz"/> and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_lwasi"/> and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼalati"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>93</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>